- The `ois` variable (line 3) is *not passed as an argument* to any external method — no `Argument` propagation.
- It is *not passed into any parameter* of a called function — no `Parameter` propagation (no method call takes `ois` as input; `ois.readObject()` is a call *on* `ois`, not *of* `ois` as arg).
- It is *not returned* — the return value is the deserialized object `(Memento) ois.readObject()`, not `ois` itself → no `Return`.
- It *is* automatically closed by the TWR construct at the end of the try block (line 4’s closing brace), i.e., after line 4 — this is a `Sink`: the resource lifecycle terminates via implicit `close()`. The release occurs in a TWR context → `ReleaseContext: twr`; and it applies on *all exit paths* (normal return, `ClassNotFoundException`, or any other exception thrown inside the try) → `GuaranteeLevel: all_exit_paths`.

No aliasing of `ois` occurs: it is final, not reassigned, and never assigned to another variable or passed elsewhere. So no indirect propagation.

